network = is web of connected items


LAN = local area network
WAN = wide area network

cybersecurity is defniteley a teamsport

A hub is a network device that broadcasts information to every device on the network. 
A router is a network device that connects multiple networks together.



TCP/IP stands for Transmission Control Protocol and Internet Protocol. TCP/IP is the standard model used for network communication.
TCP, or Transmission Control Protocol, is an internet communication protocol that allows two devices to form a connection and stream data.
The IP in TCP/IP stands for Internet Protocol. IP has a set of standards used for routing and addressing data packets as they travel between devices on a network. Included in the Internet Protocol (IP) is the IP address that functions as an address for each private network. 

